            <property name="label" translatable="yes">Sensrad employs a right-handed coordinate system. Relative to the sensor's boresight, the x-axis points
to the right, the y-axis points forward, and the z-axis points upward. The width parameter defines the
region's extent along the x-axis, the length along the y-axis, and the height along the z-axis. The yaw
angle rotates the region of interest in the x-y plane, while the pitch angle rotates it in the y-z plane.

A visualization of the region of interest is published in ROS2 under /sensrad_{id}/roi_marker</property>
            <attributes>
              <attribute name="font-desc" value="Ubuntu 10"/>
            </attributes>
          </object>
